cs.CY, cs.SI, cs.SD, cs.SOC, cs.HC

Reasoning: 
- cs.CY (Computers and Society): The paper discusses the behavior of users in a digital commons (YouTube) and how attention affects their productivity. This falls under the domain of computers and society.
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks): The paper analyzes a massive dataset from YouTube to study the relationship between attention and productivity in crowdsourcing. This involves studying the social and information networks of users on the platform.
- cs.SD (Software Engineering): The paper may also fall under software engineering as it discusses the behavior of users in a digital platform and how it affects their productivity. 
- cs.SOC (Social and Behavioral Sciences): The paper analyzes the behavior of users on YouTube and how social factors such as attention affect their productivity. This falls under the domain of social and behavioral sciences.
- cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction): The paper may also fall under human-computer interaction as it discusses how users interact with a digital platform (YouTube) and how it affects their productivity.
